<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1642,2029]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,150,394]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1643,1669]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is evidently closely related to a number of species showing a similar fore tarsus chaetotaxy and abdominal pattern, which have often been separated in their own (sub) genus, 
<emphasis box="[1126,1333,1678,1704]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Stephanodactylum</emphasis>
Rohdendorf. Apart from the 
<typeStatus box="[381,429,1715,1741]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1824" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[522,941,1714,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[522,780,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Miltogramma punctata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meigen, J. W." box="[787,941,1714,1741]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref28267" refString="Meigen, J. W. (1824) Systematische Beschreibung der bekannten europaischen zweiflugeligen Insekten, Vierter Theil. Schulz- Wundermann, Hamm, xii + 428 pp." type="book" year="1824">Meigen, 1824</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[956,1057,1714,1741]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1436,181,1075]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Left male fore tarsus. A. Miltogramma szpilai sp. nov., holotype, ventral view [mirror-image of Fig. 11C]. B. Miltogramma punctata Meigen, 1824, dorsal view [adapted from Piwczyński et al. (2017)]. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654215/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
), this taxon contains an additional five species described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[452,674,1750,1777]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf (1930)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohdendorf, 1930" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[689,1028,1750,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alajica">
<emphasis box="[689,712,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[729,807,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">alajica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[818,1028,1750,1777]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohdendorf, 1930" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[1042,1392,1750,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis box="[1042,1065,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1083,1172,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">asiatica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[1182,1392,1750,1777]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohdendorf, 1930" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dzhungarica">
<emphasis box="[1406,1429,1751,1776]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,291,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">dzhungarica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[299,506,1786,1813]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohdendorf, 1930" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[517,859,1786,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[517,540,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[555,645,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">obscura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[652,859,1786,1813]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rohdendorf, 1930" authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[918,1270,1786,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sogdiana">
<emphasis box="[918,941,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[956,1059,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">sogdiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[1066,1270,1786,1813]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[female only]. The fore tarsus of these species is equipped with long and dense setae on the anterior surface of one or more tarsomeres, combined with a cluster or tuft of six very long and strong setae, which emerge distally from the posterior part of tarsomere 4, reaching beyond and curving around the claws and the pulvilli (
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[1108,1311,1894,1921]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf 1930</bibRefCitation>
; K. Szpila, pers. comm.). However, in spite of the fore tarsal ornamentation being very characteristic and highly species-specific, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, B. B." box="[215,431,1966,1993]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref28916" refString="Rohdendorf, B. B. (1930) 64 h. Sarcophaginae. In: Lindner, E. (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. Band 11 (Lieferung 39). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1930">Rohdendorf (1930)</bibRefCitation>
made only simple notes on this feature, and it has been documented only for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[1301,1436,1967,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1301,1436,1967,1992]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within this group of species (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Seguy, E." box="[537,732,2003,2029]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 436" refId="ref29705" refString="Seguy, E. (1941) Etudes sur les mouches parasites. 2. Calliphorides, calliphorines (suite), sarcophagines et rhinophorides de l'Europe occidentale et meridionale. Encyclopedie Entomologique, Serie A, 21, 1 - 436." type="journal article" year="1941">Séguy 1941: 273</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 382; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T." box="[848,1012,2003,2029]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 203" refId="ref28438" refString="Pape, T. (1987) The Sarcophagidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 19, 1 - 203." type="journal article" year="1987">Pape 1987: 28</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 26). The abdominal pattern with three distinct, subequal black spots on tergite 3–5 is reminiscent of that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[999,1127,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis box="[999,1127,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. asiatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[1183,1320,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1183,1320,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these have the frontal vitta yellowish (posterior half in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1930" box="[702,828,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis box="[702,828,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. asiatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, entirely in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[963,1098,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[963,1098,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), while it is entirely silvery in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Xu &amp; Pape &amp; Pei &amp; Zhang, 2021" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Xu &amp; Pape &amp; Pei &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,262,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szpilai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,262,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. szpilai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,358,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[269,358,223,249]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
