<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Xu &amp; Pape &amp; Pei &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[565,638,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Miltogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szpilai">
<emphasis box="[565,638,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">szpilai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the family name of Prof. Krzysztof Szpila, in appreciation of his substantial contributions to our knowledge of Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lioy" authorityYear="1864" box="[836,1028,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Miltogramminae">Miltogramminae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
